{"session_id":"svc-1780715904317143967","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-06-06T03:18:26.000629172Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-e19185aa-20260606T031745-74d1b24c","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-e19185aa\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eReject bead dep edges that re-introduce the parent or any ancestor\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nThe decomposition action (currently invoked when a bead is too large for one execution and the agent splits it into child beads) is writing the parent\u0026#39;s ID as a dep edge on every child. This produces an unbreakable deadlock:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  e29892a4 (parent, open) -- parent --\u0026gt; child_A\u0026#xA;  e29892a4 -- parent --\u0026gt; child_B\u0026#xA;  child_A.deps = [e29892a4]           \u0026lt;- BAD: parent is also a dep\u0026#xA;  child_B.deps = [child_A, e29892a4]  \u0026lt;- BAD\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The parent stays open until its children close. Every child is blocked on the parent. Nothing can be claimed. ddx work loops on the parent, the orchestrator emits \u0026#39;mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale\u0026#39;, the worker retries, and burns claim budget without progress.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Observed scenario (niflheim, 2026-06-04 04:30-05:13 UTC):\u0026#xA;- Parent: niflheim-e29892a4 (\u0026#39;feat(delta): async write-behind ...\u0026#39;)\u0026#xA;- 10 children created during planning loops (23223661, a44a8ceb, 054c89b7, 0470ba0d, f10e9e35, f076b08c, 6c041162, 94e1df73, 9da62c2d, 5e4f9fb2)\u0026#xA;- Every child carried deps=[..siblings.., niflheim-e29892a4]\u0026#xA;- ~50 minutes of agent time + 4 strong-policy claude/opus attempts with zero feature commits; only tracker chores\u0026#xA;- Unwedged manually by closing the parent via \u0026#39;ddx bead close\u0026#39;, after which siblings drained correctly in foundational order\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Root cause is structural, not model-capability — auto-upgrading to a stronger model does NOT fix this. The orchestrator already detects the no-progress state but its only remediation is \u0026#39;retry parent\u0026#39;, which re-enters the same loop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;There is also a \u0026#39;project root mutation rejected (continuing)\u0026#39; warning emitted by the readiness check during this state; that\u0026#39;s a downstream symptom of the same problem, not the cause.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. \u0026#39;ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;bead\u0026gt; \u0026lt;dep\u0026gt;\u0026#39; HARD-REJECTS the edge when \u0026lt;dep\u0026gt; is \u0026lt;bead\u0026gt;\u0026#39;s parent OR any ancestor in the parent chain. Error message names the offending ancestor and prints the relevant parent-chain. Test: ddx_bead_dep_add_rejects_parent_ancestor.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;2. \u0026#39;ddx bead create --depends-on X --parent Y\u0026#39; with X == Y (or X an ancestor of Y) HARD-REJECTS at creation time with the same error shape as AC #1. No silent rewrite.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;3. Programmatic decomposition path (the action that fans a too-large bead into children) MUST NOT add the parent as a dep. Existing action templates / system prompts are audited and amended; one golden e2e test (decompose_does_not_self_dep) creates a bead with N children and asserts every child\u0026#39;s deps set excludes the parent.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;4. \u0026#39;ddx bead doctor\u0026#39; (existing subcommand) gains a check \u0026#39;parent_ancestor_in_deps\u0026#39; that scans the tracker, lists violating beads, and (with --fix) removes the offending edges. Output is stable / scriptable. Test: ddx_doctor_detects_and_repairs_back_edge.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;5. ddx work no-progress remediation: when an attempted bead\u0026#39;s outcome is \u0026#39;mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale\u0026#39; AND any freshly-created child carries the attempted bead in its deps, ddx auto-emits an \u0026#39;operator_attention\u0026#39; event with reason \u0026#39;parent_back_edge\u0026#39; and stops re-claiming that bead. (Today it loops indefinitely.) Test: ddx_work_halts_on_parent_back_edge.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;6. The orchestrator\u0026#39;s \u0026#39;project root mutation rejected (continuing)\u0026#39; warning, when emitted alongside the parent-back-edge state, is upgraded from WARN to ERROR with the offending bead ID logged. Test: dispatch_logs_error_on_root_mutation_with_back_edge.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;7. Lifecycle schema documents that \u0026#39;parent\u0026#39; and \u0026#39;deps\u0026#39; MUST be disjoint and that \u0026#39;deps\u0026#39; MUST be acyclic with the parent-tree. docs/ddx/lifecycle-rules.md (or equivalent) updated; ADR file if no governing artifact already exists.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;8. Existing valid graphs continue to pass \u0026#39;ddx bead doctor\u0026#39; without --fix and without regression — regression test against a pre-existing tracker snapshot.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\ndecomposed into ddx-b85090ae, ddx-1bcb9827, ddx-f9bb7327, ddx-0836dde5, ddx-4173d55c, ddx-e5511c6b\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:tracker, area:lifecycle, area:decomposition, kind:safety, kind:correctness, ac-quality:needs-refinement\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"99fd0cfea5a0481665313243cfcf75c08831b1b7\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260606T031745-74d1b24c\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-e19185aa-20260606T031745-74d1b24c/.ddx/executions/20260606T031745-74d1b24c/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-e19185aa-20260606T031745-74d1b24c/.ddx/executions/20260606T031745-74d1b24c/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/Users/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/